HEADWORD: Court-baron
<hw>Court"-bar`on</hw> <pr>(-b?r`?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>An inferior court of civil jurisdiction, attached to a manor, and held by the steward; a baron's court; -- now fallen into disuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

